               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490702-name-91" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-91" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-91" type="surname" value="RICE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-91" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN RICE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of James Rice. On 18th May Iwai coming into the shop, and saw the prisoner going out at the door with treacle pie and a dish in his hand, which were my husband's property—he had no business to take it; I had not sold it him—the policeman took him, and he said he had not taken it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had you a child in your arms? Yes—I saw his face—he turned right round—there were other boys in the street, but I am certain of him.</p>
